  "metadata": {
    "synopsis": "This drow was petrified by a spectator.Now he is unpetrified.Worries about his companions and the group's leader - the wizard. He should seem in shock. Short sentences, short delivery.Leave after a long rest.",
    "how_to_trigger": "Repro steps:1. Start the game.2. peace3. loadlevel WLD_Main_A4. goto 131.852; 49.695; -235.9485. create OBJ_Oil_Of_The_Basilisk6. Apply it on the petrified drow7. Ctrl Shift K the Spectator (if he's attacking you)8. Speak to the Drow1. One variation is use oe und_pd_freedrow. Then talk to Tecothy (S_UND_PetrifiedDrow_004).2. Second variation  is use oe und_pd_freedrow. Then ctrl+shift+K on Dhourn (S_UND_PetrifiedDrow_Wizard) to kill him before talking to Tecothy.3. Third variation is use goto 121; -235, then use god on, addDebugSpell Target_UND_Spectator_UnpetrifyingRay, and infiniteAp. Climb up the rocks to the north. A Spectator will appear and you will enter battle. Use the unpetrifying ray spell on Tecothy. Then Ctrl+Shift+K on Dhourn, Spectator, and Hook Horror. Then talk to Tecothy.4. There is a fourth variation where Dhourn is still petrified after the battle. I could not figure this out."
  },
